-position: fix 
(defines the mobility of the item within it's position)

-padding: 5px 3px 5px 3px

-float: left/right  (makes the words/boxes allign left or right)

-border: top right bottom left
border: 10px 14px 10px 14px

-margin: 10px 10px 10px 10px
or
margin-top:
margin-right:
margin-bottom:
margin-left:
The CSS margin properties are used to create space around elements, outside of any defined borders..it pushes the item around the page.

-padding works like margin would in a page, but padding only takes 
place with in a border.
padding: 10px 5px 12px 5px
or
padding-top
padding-right
padding-bottom
padding-left
The CSS padding properties are used to generate space around an element's content, inside of any defined borders.

you can creat div and nav classes....they are just common class names that developers use to just predecing thier items in the body of the page.

<section> - Defines a section in a document


The <div> tag defines a division or a section in an HTML document.
The <div> tag is used to group block-elements to format them with CSS.

<div>
<!-- this is a sections/self contain item on the page-->
</div>

<nav> - Defines a container for navigation links
</nav>

<footer> - Defines a footer for a document or a section


------------------- Responsive Web Design--------------
Responsive web are web that can scale to any size, and they respond to
the user

this is where you can use max-height, max-weidth, etc to set limits

When making responsive web pages, add the following <meta> element in all your web pages:

Example
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
